article.headline: Bradley 66, SE Missouri 65
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Taylor Brown's three-point play with 4.1 seconds to play Wednesday night lifted Bradley to a 66-65 win over Southeast Missouri State. Brown, who scored seven of his 10 points in the game's final four minutes, scored, was fouled and made the free throw. Jordan Prosser led the Braves (2-0) with 15 points and a game-high eight rebounds. Dyricus Simms-Edwards scored 13 points, Walt Lemon Jr. scored 11 and Shayok Shayok added 10 points for Bradley. Marcus Brister led all scorers with 19 points for Southeast Missouri State (1-2). Leon Powell had 15 points and Tyler Stone had 11 points and seven rebounds for the Redhawks. The game was played at Renaissance Coliseum and was Bradley's first regular-season game against a Division I opponent on campus since 1982, when the Braves last played at Robertson Fieldhouse.
